# 06_resolver_closest — proof closest_name considers all naming surfaces.
#
# Asks for `tool.nod` — a typo of `tool.node` (the only registry entry).
# Edit distance is 1. Should produce a "did you mean 'tool.node'?"
# suggestion.
#
# This validates that closest_name_across_columns walks the live
# registry as one of its candidate pools. Without that, only DB names
# would be suggested and the user typing a typo of a hand-picked name
# would get no help.
#
# Expected output:
#
#   > tool.nod click
#   error unknown object 'tool.nod' (did you mean 'tool.node'?)

tool.nod click
